 EAST\n\nThe daytime sighting of a possible Soviet BISON jet heavy bomber in the Far East was reported by the tail gunner of an American reconnaissance B-45 flying approximately 140 nautical miles south of Vladivostok on 9 December. The gunner reported seeing a large aircraft with a swept-wing configuration and a right tip tank. It approached from behind and paced the American aircraft at approximately 38,000 feet for about five minutes at a distance of from 5 to 30 miles, then dropped back and disappeared.\n\nComment\n\nThis is the first indication that there may be a BISON jet heavy bomber in the Soviet Far East. The description of a swept-wing aircraft could also apply to the BADGER (TU-16) jet medium bomber and to the BEAR turbo-prop heavy bomber. Of these three aircraft, only the BISON, however, has a pod on each wing tip which could be described as a \"tip tank", "token_count": 161, "token_end_0based": 160, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "6 possible soviet jet heavy bomber sighted in far east the daytime sighting of a possible soviet bison jet heavy bomber in the far east was reported by the tail gunner of an american reconnaissance b-45 flying approximately 140 nautical miles south of vladivostok on 9 december the gunner reported seeing a large aircraft with a swept-wing configuration and a right tip tank it approached from behind and paced the american aircraft at approximately 38 000 feet for about five minutes at a distance of from 5 to 30 miles then dropped back and disappeared comment this is the first indication that there may be a bison jet heavy bomber in the soviet far east the description of a swept-wing aircraft could also apply to the badger tu-16 jet medium bomber and to the bear turbo-prop heavy bomber of these three aircraft only the bison however has a pod on each wing tip which could be described as a tip tank", "unred_source_page": 9}
